 * 
 * Notes:
 * - NSA: Not Seasonally Adjusted index used for most inflation derivatives
 * - Year-on-Year (YoY) Swaps: Pays the annual inflation rate each period
 * - Zero-coupon Inflation Swaps: Pays the cumulative inflation rate at maturity
 * - Indexation Lag: The delay between the inflation index publication and its use in calculations
 * - Interpolation Method: Used to calculate reference inflation index between monthly publications
 * - TIPS: Treasury Inflation-Protected Securities (US)
 * - Breakeven Inflation Rate: Difference between nominal bond yield and inflation-linked bond real yield
 * - Principal Protection: Most inflation-linked bonds have a principal guarantee at par (floor at 100)
 * - Index Publication Frequency: Monthly for most countries, quarterly for Australia
 * - Cash Settlement: Most inflation derivatives settle in cash based on the official index value
 * - Inflation Caps/Floors: Option structures that provide protection against high/low inflation
 * - Standard Maturities: 1Y, 2Y, 3Y, 5Y, 7Y, 10Y, 15Y, 20Y, 30Y
 * - Reference Indices:
 *   - US CPI-U: US Consumer Price Index for All Urban Consumers
 *   - HICP: Harmonized Index of Consumer Prices (Euro area)
 *   - RPI: Retail Price Index (UK)
 *   - JCG CPI: Japan Consumer Price Index
 *   - AU CPI: Australian Consumer Price Index
 *   - CA CPI: Canada Consumer Price Index
 *   - SE CPI: Sweden Consumer Price Index
 *   - CH CPI: Switzerland Consumer Price Index
