 * Special Cases and Additional Notes:
 * 
 * 1. Interpolation: Linear interpolation is standard for non-publication dates across all currencies
 * 
 * 2. Seasonality: 
 *    - EUR and USD: Seasonal adjustments often applied
 *    - GBP: Typically no seasonal adjustments
 * 
 * 3. Structure Types:
 *    - Zero-coupon: Most common globally, single payment at maturity
 *    - Year-on-year: Common in EUR markets
 *    - LPI (Limited Price Indexation): Common in GBP markets (with caps/floors)
 * 
 * 4. Publication Schedule:
 *    - All indices typically published monthly
 *    - Publication delays vary slightly by country (2-3 weeks after month end)
 *    - Indexation lag accounts for publication delays
 *
 * 5. Holiday Calendars:
 *    - USD: US Federal holidays
